‌CHAPTER 5
20 January 1976 pm in Chuang Tzu Auditorium
[A sannyasin asks: How is it possible always to remain centred? There is a tendency to go astray...
]
Don’t create any conflict about going astray and being centred. Float. If you create a conflict, if you become afraid of going astray, then there is more possibility that you will go astray – because whatsoever you try to suppress becomes very significant.
